title: ‘End of the world’: Artificial Intelligence’s rapid growth sparks major concern
description: Sky News host Caleb Bond says Artificial Intelligence will be the “end of the world” if people are not careful.

title: ‘Enormous uptick’ in new apps downloaded after children social media ban
description: Former Liberal senator Hollie Hughes says there has been an “enormous uptick” in new apps downloaded after the under-16s social media ban.

title: China ‘under strain’ as iron ore producers become more competitive
description: Geologist Ian Plimer says China is potentially “under strain” with suppliers of steel becoming more competitive.   “West Africa now will be putting 100 million tonnes of iron ore on the market,” Mr Plimer told Sky News Senior Reporter Caroline Marcus.  “That puts the Chinese under strain … we can make steel cheaper than China can.”

title: ‘Can’t think of anywhere better’: Gold Coast emerges as Trump Tower hotspot
description: Former Liberal senator Hollie Hughes reacts to future plans of a Trump Tower being developed in Australia’s Gold Coast.   “Australia may be his next venture, there’s talk of the Trump Tower coming to the Gold Coast, and I have got to say I can’t think of anywhere better for Trump Tower to go,” Ms Hughes said.  “It’ll match all those gold sandals with white shorts that already get out on the Gold Coast beaches over the summer.   “I think this’d be awesome.”

title: ‘Big problem’: Allan government under fire over bushfire response
description: Shadow regional development minister Anne Webster says it’s a “big problem” how the Allan government has handled Victorian bushfires.   “In my patch it’s certainly been devastating to be amongst my community and see the ravaging of a bushfire,” Ms Webster told Sky News host James Morrow.  “I’ve spoken at length this week about the lack of preparation, the lack of burn-offs … because of Victoria’s laws to keep the highways clean of grass.”

title: ‘Seismic’: Robert Jenrick defects to Farage’s Reform UK
description: Former Reform UK candidate Mayuran Sentilnathan says Robert Jenrick has defected to Nigel Farage’s Reform UK.   “This is a seismic defection, this isn’t an ordinary person crossing the floor from the Conservative Party to Reform,” Mr Sentilnathan told Sky News host James Morrow.  “He [Robert Jenrick] went into the home office and was effectively radicalised by the incompetence of the government and how they couldn’t control their borders.”

title: Australia ‘going after’ Grok for its AI misuse
description: Sky News host Caleb Bond says the Australian government is “going after” X for the misuse of its AI service Grok.

title: ‘Awesome’: Gold Coast may become home to Trump Tower
description: Former Liberal senator Hollie Hughes says there are rumours of Trump Tower coming to the Gold Coast in Australia.   “Someone who can never be accused of having low expectations at all is Donald Trump,” Ms Hughes said.  “Australia may be his next venture; there’s talk of the Trump Tower coming to the Gold Coast … this would be awesome.”

title: ‘Clamp down on free speech’: Influencer Eva Vlaardingerbroek's visa ban analysed
description: Former Reform UK candidate Mayuran Sentilnathan comments on influencer Eva Vlaardingerbroek’s visa ban from the UK.  “Socialists love big states … a big state needs authoritarianism to run itself, and authoritarianism needs to clamp down on free speech, free speech is the great enemy of the socialists,” Mr Sentilnathan told Sky News host James Morrow.  “She [Eva Vlaardingerbroek] is aligned with Tommy Robinson.”

title: First month of children social media ban sees 4.7 million accounts deactivated
description: Sky News contributor Joe Hildebrand says more than 4.7 million accounts held by children on social media have been deactivated in the first month of Australia’s social media ban.

title: ‘Plenty’ of children getting around Australia’s social media ban
description: Sky News host Caleb Bond says there’s “plenty” of children getting around Australia’s social media ban.

title: Gold Coast is one of the ‘fastest growing cities’ in Australia
description: Sky News host Caleb Bond says the Gold Coast is one of the “fastest growing cities” in Australia.

title: ‘Gaslighting’: Jacinta Allan’s handling of Victorian bushfires
description: Shadow regional development minister Anne Webster criticises the Victorian government’s response to bushfires, claiming the Allan government has been “gaslighting”.   “They’ve had Royal Commissions, they’ve had recommendations, they have not acted,” Ms Webster told Sky News host James Morrow.  “The gaslighting that has gone on this week, from the premier, regarding the CFA … it’s just not good enough.”

title: Labor ‘cynically taking advantage’ of Bondi massacre with new hate speech legislation
description: Sky News host James Morrow says Labor is trying to “ram through” its new hate speech legislation.  Mr Morrow said the government is “cynically taking advantage” of the Bondi terror attack.  “To create a vast new apparatus that could send Australians to jail for up to five years simply because they used 'hurty' words even if no one was actually hurt by them.”

title: ‘Job hugging’ is new term for people wanting to keep their employment
description: Sky News host Caleb Bond says there’s a new term for people wanting to keep their employment called “job hugging”.
